HEADWORD: Rhatanhy
<hw>Rhat"an*hy</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>ratania</ets>, <ets>rata⟦ntil⟧a</ets>,
Peruv. <ets>rata⟦ntil⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <def>The powerfully astringent
root of a half-shrubby Peruvian plant (<spn>Krameria triandra</spn>). It
is used in medicine and to color port wine.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>ratany</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Savanilla rhatany</b></col>, <cd>the root of
